武汉新冠肺炎疫情肆虐，每一个家庭都在举全家之力，从防疫生死线上拽住家人。
Wuhan Xinguan pneumonia epidemic rages, every family is lifting the family strength, from the life-and-death of the epidemic to drag the family.
患者、家庭、医院……求医与救治环环相扣。
Patients, families, hospitals... seek medical treatment and treatment are interlinked.
有的人最终去世，更多的人在治愈出院，在历经煎熬、等待、悲痛、喜悦之后，用人心和勇气筑起的这道防疫线，正在变得牢固而强健。
Some are finally dead, and many more are becoming strong and strong as they heal and discharge the epidemic line that was built with hearts and courage after suffering, waiting, grieving and rejoicing.
全文5012字，阅读约需10分钟点击下图进入阅读新京报特别策划新京报记者 王瑞锋 祖一飞 韩茹雪 王飞翔 王翀鹏程 梁静怡编辑 胡杰 校对 吴兴发扩散是逐渐的。
The Beijing News Special Planning Commission Special Planning Report Wang Ruifeng Zu Feifei Wang Lu Ju Flying Wang Zhengyi Zhang Peng Cheng Liang Jingyi editor Hu Jie proofread Wu Xingfa proliferation is gradual.
起初是两个，三个，几个白色斑点，接着连成一片，白色阴影从右肺蔓延到左肺。
At first it was two, three, a few white spots, then one, and the white shadow spread from the right lung to the left lung.
在医生办公室，胡安平清楚地从光片上看到自己肺里的那些白色斑点。
In the doctor's office, Hu Anping clearly saw the white spots on his lungs.
2019年12月底，53岁的湖北人胡安平觉得全身乏力、咳嗽、发冷，盖着三床被子还觉得冷，到当地医院就诊时，被诊断为肺炎。
At the end of December 2019, Hu Anping, a 53-year-old Hubei, felt weak, coughed and chilled, cold under three quilts, and was diagnosed with pneumonia when he went to a local hospital.
打了两天针，再去拍片子，主治医生告诉家人，情况很严重，准备下“病重通知书”。
After two days of injections and then to make a film, the attending doctor told his family that the situation was serious, ready to issue a "serious illness notice."
1月5日下午，胡安平被救护车送到武汉中南医院，确诊为新型冠状病毒肺炎感染者，成为湖北最早一批确诊的患者。
January 5 afternoon, Hu Anping was transported by ambulance to Wuhan Zhongnan Hospital, confirmed as a new coronavirus pneumonia, Hubei the first group of confirmed patients.
病毒来势凶猛。
The virus is coming.
第二天，肺已经成为“白肺”，高烧，呼吸困难，胡安平被送进重症监护室。
The next day, the lung has become "white lung," high fever, breathing difficulties, Hu Anping was placed in intensive care unit.
如同肺叶上飞快弥散的斑点阴影，大量疑似和确诊病人开始涌现，各家医院都人满为患。
As the speckled shadows on the lungs spread rapidly, a large number of suspected and diagnosed patients began to emerge, and hospitals were overcrowded.
患者、家庭、医院……求医与救治环环相扣，防疫线上，却是生死之间。
Patients, families, hospitals... seek medical treatment and treatment of interlocking, epidemic prevention line, but between life and death.
有的人最终去世，更多的人在治愈出院，在历经煎熬、等待、悲痛、喜悦之后，用人心和勇气筑起的这道防疫线，正在变得牢固而强健。
Some are finally dead, and many more are becoming strong and strong as they heal and discharge the epidemic line that was built with hearts and courage after suffering, waiting, grieving and rejoicing.
━━━━━“照顾母亲，我明知会被传染也要来”胡安平至今也不知道自己是什么时候染的病，刚开始发病的时候，跟感冒一样，咳嗽，发冷。
I know that I will come too. Hu Anping still does not know when he contracted the disease. When he first got sick, he coughed and chilled like a cold.
他在黄冈菜市场卖家禽，市场里的海鲜大多是从武汉华南海鲜市场进货，他怀疑自己的染病或与此有关。
He sells poultry at the Huanggang Halles Market, where seafood is mostly imported from Wuhan South China Seafood Market. He suspects his illness is related to it.
和胡安平一样，大部分人都是在不知不觉中染病。
Like Hu Anping, most people get sick before they know it.
▲南方医科大学南方医院支援湖北疫情防控医疗队队员在武汉汉口医院援助。
Southern Medical University Southern Hospital support Hubei epidemic prevention and control team members in Wuhan Hankou Hospital assistance.
受访者供图38岁的王逸飞是武汉的一名老师。
The interviewee shows Wang Yifai, 38, as a teacher in Wuhan.
封城前几天，她和丈夫、孩子来到黑龙江雪乡，却没想到意外地逃过一劫。
A few days before the closure of the city, she and her husband, children came to Heilongjiang Snow Township, but unexpectedly escaped a robbery.
疫情暴发后，她留在武汉的父母和弟弟、弟媳先后出现异常。
After the outbreak of the outbreak, her parents and brothers in Wuhan, sister-in-law have appeared abnormal.
遍寻医院后，四人均确诊感染新冠肺炎。
After searching the hospital, the four patients were diagnosed with new crown pneumonia.
弟媳的预产期不到20天，1月23日，武汉封城，地铁、公交停运，出租车、网约车也很难打到。
Sister-in-law's expected date of birth is less than 20 days, January 23, Wuhan sealing city, subway, bus stop, taxis, network cars are also difficult to hit.
为了能让怀孕的老婆住上院，发烧39摄氏度的弟弟开着私家车，带着全家人到处找医院。
In order to let the pregnant wife live in the upper house, a brother with a fever of 39 degrees Celsius drove in a private car and took his family everywhere to the hospital.
40多岁的林安，一个长江边长大的武汉人，也在猝不及防中染上了病毒。
Lin'an, a 40-year-old Wuhan native who grew up along the Yangtze River, was caught off guard by the virus.
唯一能确定的是，1月20日，他曾在硚口区一个地下市场采购过年货，“那个市场每天都有几千人进出，而且很封闭”。
The only certainty is that on January 20, he purchased New Year's goods from an underground market in Zhangkou district, "where thousands of people go in and out every day and are very closed."
更重要的是，他没有戴口罩。
More importantly, he was not wearing a mask.
他是家里第一个出现症状的，接着他的妻子开始持续发热，随后70多岁的岳母也开始发烧、乏力、食欲不振。
He was the first to develop symptoms in his family, and then his wife became feverish, followed by her mother-in-law in her 70s with fever, fatigue and loss of appetite.
“岳母本身就患有高血压、哮喘，身体一向不好。
"My mother-in-law has high blood pressure, asthma and is always in poor health.
”林安担心，岳母扛不住这种到现在都没有找到传染源的病毒。
Lin worried that her mother-in-law could not carry the virus, which had not been found to date.
武汉汉阳区的李丽娜2月1日在跟母亲赵巧英一次视频通话时，发现母亲状况不对，咳嗽十分严重。
Wuhan Hanyang District Li Lina and her mother Zhao Qiaoying in a video conversation on February 1, found the mother is in the wrong situation, very serious cough.
赵巧英独居，春节前参加了老友聚会，李丽娜专门提醒她，这个病很有风险，不要去人多的地方。
Zhao Qiaoying lived alone, the Spring Festival before the old friends party, Li Lina specially reminded her that this disease is very risky, do not go to places where many people.
赵巧英没有听，“她跟我说，别人都说了，这个病没那么吓人，你看这么多人在街上走。
Zhao Qiaoying did not listen to me, "she told me, others have said, the disease is not so scary, you see so many people walking in the street.
”发现状况不对的李丽娜立即赶到母亲家，带着赵巧英到武汉中医院检查，赵巧英发烧接近39摄氏度，CT影像学显示双肺感染，有磨玻璃状阴影，氧饱和度数值92，被列入疑似病患。
Discovering that Li Lina, who was in the wrong condition, rushed to her mother's house and took Zhao Qiaoying to Wuhan Chinese Hospital for examination. Chao Qiaoying had a fever of nearly 39 degrees Celsius. CT imaging showed two lung infections, abrasive glass shadows, oxygen saturation value 92 and was classified as a suspected patient.
来接母亲之前，李丽娜已经做好了充足的心理准备，“照顾母亲，我明知会被传染也要来，没什么办法，只能扛着。
Before she came to pick up her mother, she was well prepared to take care of her mother. "I knew I would be infected and had no choice but to carry it.
”她专门做了防护，除了口罩，还戴了一副只有旅游时才戴的墨镜。
She made special protection, except for a mask, and wore a pair of sunglasses, which were worn only for travel.
这一年春节，李丽娜原本计划自驾游，和老公、孩子一起开车去广西、广东游玩。
During the Spring Festival, Li Lina had planned to drive to Guangxi and Guangdong with her husband and children.
“1月下旬，看到患病人数在增长，电视上号召武汉人不要出远门，就决定不去自驾游了。
"In late January, seeing the number of cases growing, the TV called on Wuhan people to stay away from home and decided not to drive their own cars.
”李丽娜说。
'she said.
临时决定不出门，一家人没有准备年货，除夕夜只做了一顿简单的饭菜。
Temporary decision not to go out, the family did not prepare New Year's Eve, only made a simple meal.
唯一庆幸的是，李丽娜让母亲来家里吃年夜饭，赵巧英没来，“不然一家人全被传染。
Only luckily, Li Lina let her mother come home to dinner, Zhao Qiaoying did not come, "otherwise the whole family is infected.
”━━━━━“没经历过的人，根本体会不到有多难”进重症监护室之前，胡安平几乎两天两夜没有睡觉，“家人都在身边鼓励我，说不管花多少钱都会给我治病，一定会等着我。
People who haven't experienced it don't know how hard it is to get into intensive care, Hu Anping didn't sleep for almost two days and nights. "My family was there to encourage me and say that no matter how much money I would spend, he would wait for me.
但我不敢睡，怕睡过去就醒不过来了。
But I dare not sleep, for fear of going to sleep and not wake up.
”家里托人从外面买了进口药，一组有5瓶，每瓶700元，一天就用3500元。
There were five bottles of imported medicine in one group for 700 yuan each, or 3,500 yuan a day.
消炎针水从早吊到晚，几乎没有断过。
The anti-inflammatory needle hung from morning till night, almost without interruption.
与王逸飞和李丽娜两家人相比，作为最早一批的患者，能确诊，住进医院，胡安平甚至算是幸运。
Compared with Wang Yifai and Li Lina family, as the earliest group of patients, can be diagnosed, admitted to the hospital, Hu Anping is even lucky.
王逸飞的父母退休前是医生，会打针，托朋友搞到些抗病毒的药，“每天早晨，爸、妈和我弟互相给对方打针，但也没什么效果，弟弟接着开车往医院跑。
"Every morning, Dad, Mom and my brother gave each other shots, but to no avail. My brother drove off to the hospital.
”王逸飞说，她弟弟曾一天跑了五家医院，从早上八点一直跑到凌晨四点，还有60多岁发着高烧的父母一起在医院耗着，到最后也没有找到床位。
Mr. Wang says her brother visited five hospitals a day, running from 8 a.m. to 4 a.m., and parents in their sixties, suffering from high fever, spent time together in the hospital and were unable to find beds.
王逸飞一家人的中心是孕妇。
The center of the Wang Yifai family is pregnant.
预产期只剩10天的时候，为了能保住儿媳妇，王逸飞的妈妈在医院给医生下跪，“但是没用，真的没有床位，只能一遍遍往医院跑，医院里全是排队的人，想跟医生说上话都至少要等两三个小时。
With only 10 days to go before the due date, Wang Yifai's mother knelt down at the hospital for the sake of keeping her daughter-in-law alive. "But it doesn't work.
”连日来，整个家庭处于崩溃边缘，婆媳两人整日以泪洗面，神情木讷。
For days, the whole family was on the verge of collapse, and the wife-in-law wept and looked dull.
排队，等待，漫长的煎熬，跟王逸飞一家一样，每一个家庭都在举全家之力，从防疫生死线上拽住家人。
Queuing, waiting, long suffering, and Wang Yifai family, every family is lifting the family strength, from the life and death of the disease to drag the family.
▲2月15日 武汉。
15 February, Wuhan.
援助武汉新冠肺炎疫情的医疗队员结束数小时的值班后，冒雪回到驻地。
Medical crews on duty for several hours after assisting the Wuhan Hengguan Pneumonia outbreak returned to their posts in snow.
新京报记者陶冉 摄李丽娜的母亲赵巧英2月1日被列入疑似患者后，一直在等待核酸检测。
Li's mother, Zhao Qiaoying, a reporter for the Beijing News, has been waiting for nucleic acid tests since she was listed as a suspect on February 1.
李丽娜每天一早带着母亲在武汉中医院做常规治疗，打消炎针加激素治疗，晚上回家安顿好母亲，用消毒液给家里消毒，热水蒸煮碗筷，忙到凌晨两点多。
Li Lina took her mother to Wuhan Chinese Hospital every morning for routine treatment, anti-inflammatory needle plus hormone treatment, at night home good mother, disinfection with disinfectant, hot cooking chopsticks, busy until more than 2 a.m.
因为住不进院，她甚至把家里布置成了小医院。
Unable to get into the hospital, she even set it up as a small hospital.
去药店花2300元买了台制氧机，又花一万多元买了台呼吸机，还有雾化机和紫外线消毒灯。
I went to the pharmacy and bought an oxygen machine for 2300 yuan and a ventilator for more than 10,000 yuan, plus an atomizer and ultraviolet disinfectant lamp.
2月5日，赵巧英终于做成了核酸检测。
On February 5, Zhao Qiaoying finally made a nucleic acid test.
但同天她病情加重，发烧近40摄氏度，呼吸困难。
But the same day she became seriously ill, with a fever of nearly 40 degrees Celsius and breathing difficulties.
CT复查显示，双肺感染面积扩大，呈白肺状。
CT review showed that the area of bilateral lung infection expanded, white lung shape.
与此同时，李丽娜发烧到39.2摄氏度，感觉自己也被感染了。
Meanwhile, Lilina, with a fever of 39.2 degrees Celsius, felt herself infected.
三天后的2月8日下午，李丽娜接到医院电话通知，“介于阴性和阳性之间，为了准确，明天再来采样重新检查。
Three days later, on the afternoon of February 8, Li Lina received a phone call from the hospital saying, "Between negative and positive, we'll take samples and re-examine them tomorrow for accuracy.
”李丽娜说，她接到这个电话后，觉得已经绝望了。
"Li said she felt desperate when she got the call.
彼时，赵巧英人离不开制氧机，大小便失禁，已经不能下床。
At that time, Zhao Qiaoying could not leave the oxygen machine, incontinence, can not get out of bed.
当努力和心血一点点耗尽之后，绝望是一下子涌出来的。
When the effort and effort are exhausted, the despair comes out all at once.
无奈之下，李丽娜走上24楼阳台，用汤勺敲击脸盆求助，凄厉的哭声在楼宇间回荡，“大家谁能来帮我下，我实在是没办法了，我在这里敲锣，我也不想传染大家。
However, Li Lina walked to the balcony on the 24th floor, with a soup spoon hit the basin for help, the shrill cry echoed across the building, "I can not help you, I can not help, I knock here, I do not want to infect everyone.
”有人报了警，警察来了，但没有上楼。
The policeman was called, but did not go upstairs.
社区打来电话劝慰，邻居冲她喊话，安慰她，说她可以去火神山医院。
When the community called to soothe her, neighbors shouted at her, comforting her by saying she could go to Mount Fire Hospital.
当晚，适逢元宵节。
That night, the Lantern Festival.
李丽娜说，她平常是一个体面人，在公开场合大声哭喊是她特别讨厌的行为，“可我觉得我要失去母亲的时候，而且亲眼看着她从我怀里离开的时候，我受不了了，也顾不了脸面。
'She was usually a respectable person, and crying in public was a particular nuisance to her, 'but I felt I could not bear to lose my mother, and could not bear to look at her as she left me.
没经历过的人，根本体会不到有多难。
People who haven't experienced it don't know how difficult it is.
”林安最开始的担忧，还是成为了现实。
Mr Lin's initial fears became a reality.
1月29日，妻子最先诊断为新冠肺炎。
His wife was first diagnosed with pneumonia on January 29.
2月6日，他和岳母的检测结果出来，都是阳性，但是医院还是没有床位。
On February 6, he and his mother-in-law tested positive, but the hospital still had no beds.
他依旧每天开车带着家人到医院输液。
He still drives his family to the hospital every day for infusions.
两天后，岳母昏迷。
Two days later, his mother-in-law passed out.
社区帮忙联系了一台救护车，就近送到了武汉普爱医院观察室。
The community helped to contact an ambulance and brought it close to Wuhan Puri Hospital Observation Room.
观察室门口，废纸箱堆积如山，里面原来装的，都是当下用量最大的几种常见药。
Observation room door, waste cardboard boxes piled up in the mountains, the original contents, are the current use of the largest number of common drugs.
在纸箱堆和双开门的观察室中间，林安的岳母度过了生命的最后5分钟。
Lian's mother-in-law spent the last five minutes of her life between the carton stack and the double-open observation room.
“人就像树叶一样，风一吹就没了”。
Man is like a leaf. The wind blows away.
林安说，这是一家三口接连被确诊为新冠肺炎后，他第一次哭了出来。
Lin said he cried for the first time since three people were diagnosed with pneumonia one after another.
这个普通的武汉老太太，作为一个数字，和武汉其他新冠肺炎的62名死者，一起出现在当天官方的通报上。
The common Wuhan woman, as a figure, along with 62 other deaths from Wuhan's new crown pneumonia, appeared on the day of the official announcement.
━━━━━“有人退出，就要有人补上来，我不去做谁去做”在重症监护室住了三天，胡安平终于有了知觉，但还是觉得冷。
I'm not going to do it. "After three days in the intensive care unit, Hu finally came to his senses, but he still felt cold.
他戴着呼吸机没法说话，只能用手指示意。
He could not speak with a respirator, but only with his fingers.
四肢无力，连一只饺子都拿不起来，只能让护士喂饭。
Weak limbs, even a dumpling can not be held up, can only let the nurse feed.
给病人喂饭，只是护士日常琐碎工作中最平常的一部分。
Feeding the sick is only the most common part of a nurse's daily routine.
“在病房里就是凭良心做事，我们穿着防护服，别人也分不清谁是谁。
"It's conscience in the room, we're wearing protective clothing and people don't know who it is.
”陈玉如说。
"said Chen.
她是金银潭医院工作多年的护士，从一开始就参与抗击新型肺炎的工作。
She worked as a nurse at Gold and Silver Pool Hospital for many years and was involved in the fight against the new pneumonia from the beginning.
“很多病人睡在床上动不了，缺氧动一下浑身难受，晚上我们巡视时，做的大量工作是端尿壶、帮他们翻身。
"A lot of patients don't sleep in bed, they don't have enough oxygen and they feel sick all over," he says.
有的人尿床，你给不给他换床单被子?你是看见有尿就倒还是等它满了再倒，都是凭良心。
Some people bed-wetting, you do not change the bedspread quilt for him? You see the urine, or wait until it's full, it's all conscience.
”她说。
'she said.
除了繁忙的工作压力，心理压力同样巨大。
In addition to the hectic work pressure, the psychological pressure is also huge.
金银潭医院护士孙小小说，每个人情绪都很紧绷，有时候一个人吃着饭，跟家人打电话，跟朋友拌嘴，看手机的时候，会突然崩溃，“但不会在病人面前哭泣，那会增加感染风险。
Sometimes a person eating alone, talking on the phone with his family, quarrelling with friends, looking at a cell phone can suddenly collapse. But it doesn't make you cry in front of the patient, which increases the risk of infection
”这个24岁的女孩坦言，她也怕死，并不想上前线，但疫情暴发后，她连续工作了41天没有休息。
The 24-year-old confessed that she too was afraid of death and did not want to go to the front line, but after the outbreak she worked for 41 days without a break.
“有人退出，就要有人补上来，我不做谁去做?我是抱着最坏的想法去的，没有往好的地方想。
"If someone quits, someone will make it up, and I won't do it. I'm going with the worst, not the best.
”陈玉如同样害怕感染。
Chen is equally afraid of infection.
在她的双肩包里，特意放了一本史铁生的《病隙碎笔》，她担心自己万一感染被隔离，“带一本书可以打发时间。
In her shoulder bag, she placed a copy of Shi Tiesheng's "Breakthrough of Disease," fearing that she might be quarantined in case of infection. "Take a book and pass the time
”提起女医护人员，医生蔡毅说，大家都在上班，这不是刻意表现，“一个两个上去有些怕，大家在一起就不害怕。
"When it comes to female medical staff, doctor Cai Yi said," Everyone is at work, which is not a deliberate act.
”蔡毅是武汉市中心医院后湖院区疼痛科主任，今年39岁，他所在医院是距华南海鲜市场最近的三甲医院，也是最早收治新冠肺炎患者的医院之一。
Cai Yi, 39, director of pain at the Houhu courtyard of Wuhan Central Hospital, is the closest Triple A hospital to the South China seafood market and one of the first hospitals to treat patients with pneumonia.
蔡毅说，中心医院人手不够了，先是内科医生上前线，然后是他这样的外科医生也参与过去。
Cai said the central hospital was understaffed, first by a physician on the front line and then by a surgeon like him.
整个武汉的医疗团队都在前线。
The entire Wuhan medical team is on the front line.
南方医院感染内科肝脏肿瘤中心教授郭亚兵是南方医院赴武汉医疗队的队长。
Southern Hospital Infection Internal Liver Oncology Center Professor Guo Yabing is the South Hospital to Wuhan Medical Team Leader.
郭亚兵和队友们负责汉口医院呼吸六科，管理76张病床。
Guo and his teammates are responsible for six breathing departments at Hankou Hospital, managing 76 beds.
最紧张的时候， 1500人到2000人的门诊量，走廊、过道都是病人，汉口医院呼吸科和ICU的医生有感染的，也有累倒的，“扛了近三个星期”。
At the height of the stress, between 1,500 and 2,000 outpatient visits, hallways and aisles were filled with patients, and doctors at Hankou Hospital's respiratory department and ICU were infected and overworked, "for nearly three weeks."
郭亚兵说，专家们为了救人，都急红了眼。
Guo Yabing said experts were red-eyed to save lives.
汉口医院原本只能供30多人同时用氧，病人多氧气不够，他们想到了最原始的方法，使用氧气瓶来替代。
Hankou Hospital could only supply more than 30 people with oxygen at the same time. Patients did not have enough oxygen. They thought of the original method and used oxygen cylinders instead.
大家每天来来回回地去扛瓶子，一个氧气瓶子有百来斤重。
Each day they came and went to carry the bottle, one of which weighed about one kilo.
有的病人一个小时一瓶就用没了，抢救病人时旁边要摆放三五个钢瓶。
Some patients use one bottle per hour, save the patient next to put three or five cylinders.
随着全国各地医疗队的驰援，病人收治逐渐从无序转向有序。
With the assistance of medical teams all over the country, the patient admission gradually from disorder to order.
从2月17日开始，蔡毅被医院强制休息两周，“外地医生都到武汉驰援，我不想休息，医院都逼着我休息。
From Feb. 17, Cai Yi was forced to rest in hospital for two weeks. "Doctors from other places came to Wuhan to help me.
”“医生，能够轮岗，一批换一批，基本可以保证工作两周，休息两周。
"Doctor, I can rotate, I can change lots, and I can basically guarantee a fortnight's work and a two-week rest.
护士呢，没有足够的后备军，所以只能轮换，不能轮岗。
Nurse, there is not enough reserve, so can only rotate, not rotation.
在医院里，医生有事病人有事，都喊护士。
At the hospital, the doctor called the nurse if he had anything to do with the patient.
”2月14日，蔡毅发表长文《女人长城》，记录了护士工作的艰辛。
On February 14, Cai Yi published a long article, "The Great Wall of Women," documenting the hardships of a nurse's job.
他在文章中写道：一名在岗护士给他发微信说，发烧了，做了个CT一看，右肺，白一大片。
One of the nurses on duty wrote to him that he had a fever, a CT scan and a large white lung.
“甚至有个护士同事跟我说，压力太大，可能受不了要辞职。
"I even had a nurse colleague who told me that I was stressed out and probably couldn't stand quitting.
我问她，现在吗?她轻轻地说，疫情之后。
I asked her, now? She whispered, after the outbreak.
”━━━━━“感恩所有帮助过我们的人”出院之后的日子，胡安平称之为“第二段人生”。
Gratitude To All Those Who Helped Us In the days following his discharge from hospital, Hu called it Second Life.
1月28日，他正式出院，在媒体的报道中，他是武汉疫情中第一位出院的重症患者。
On January 28, he was officially discharged from the hospital. According to media reports, he was the first serious patient to be discharged from the Wuhan epidemic.
▲2020年2月16日，办理完出院手续的新冠肺炎患者。
On February 16, 2020, the completion of the discharge formalities for patients with New Crown Pneumonia.
新京报记者陶冉 摄如今，胡安平还在武汉一家宾馆里自行隔离。
Tao Ran, a reporter for the Beijing News, is now isolated in a Wuhan hotel.
他不出门，每天呆在宾馆里刷新闻，最关心疫情的进展。
He did not go out, every day in the hotel brush the news, the most concerned about the progress of the epidemic.
儿子给他买了面包、饼干、方便面，妻子一个人留守在黄冈的家中，每天和胡安平通三个电话，互相报平安。
His son bought him bread, biscuits, instant noodles, and his wife stayed alone at his home in Huanggang.
“等武汉解除封城，我马上回黄冈，现在就想和妻子好好说说话。
"When Wuhan is lifted, I will go back to Huanggang. I want to talk to my wife now.
”胡安平说。
"said Hu.
1月28日，武汉市新型肺炎防控指挥部医疗救治组发布文件，要求相关医疗机构做好孕妇等特殊病人的医疗保障工作。
On January 28, the medical treatment group of Wuhan New Pneumonia Prevention and Control Command issued a document requiring relevant medical institutions to provide medical care for pregnant women and other special patients.
就在胡安平出院的第二天，在社区努力协调近10个小时后，一家综合性医院决定接收王逸飞的弟媳，她最终顺利生下一个女孩，成为全家唯一没有被感染的人。
The day after he was discharged from hospital, nearly 10 hours after community efforts to coordinate, a general hospital decided to accept Wang Yifai's sister-in-law, who eventually gave birth to a girl who became the only person in the family not to be infected.
“敲锣救母”的第二天，李丽娜接到汉阳医院的电话，让母亲赵巧英入院治疗。
"percussion to save mother" the next day, Li Lina received a call from Hanyang Hospital, let mother Zhao Qiaoying hospital treatment.
几天后，李丽娜也确诊，先被送往武汉国博方舱医院治疗，后转入武汉第五人民医院。
A few days later, Li Lina was also diagnosed, was first sent to Wuhan Guobo cabin hospital for treatment, and then transferred to Wuhan Fifth People's Hospital.
在去方舱医院之前，她把呼吸机捐给了汉阳医院。
She donated the ventilator to Hanyang Hospital before going to the Fang Causeway Hospital.
“呼吸机对于肺炎病人很重要，医院也缺少这些设备，我母亲得到了救治，所以呼吸机给更多人，才能体现价值。
"Breathing machines are important to patients with pneumonia, hospitals lack them, my mother gets treatment, so the ventilator gives more people value.
”岳母去世之后，林安被协和医院收治，妻子在方舱医院，他们的状况正在好转。
After his mother-in-law died, Lin was admitted to Concorde Hospital and his wife was in Fang She Hospital, where their condition was improving.
两周前，王逸飞的弟媳愈后出院。
Two weeks ago, Wang Yifai's sister-in-law was discharged.
她的父母、弟弟仍在医院中治疗，三人情况均已好转。
Her parents and brother are still in hospital and all three are in better health.
一家人给孩子取了个小名——恩恩， “意思是，让她记得感恩，感恩所有帮助过我们的人。
The family gave the child a nickname, "En," meaning, "Let her remember to be grateful, to be grateful to all those who helped us.
”▲2020年2月19日，一名重症患者康复后由车辆送回社区。
On February 19, 2020, a critically ill patient recovered and was returned to the community by car.
新京报记者 陶冉 摄2月17日至19日，一场前所未有的大排查，在武汉三镇3300多个社区、村湾同步展开，要求不落一户、不漏一人。
Tao Ran, a reporter for the Beijing News, conducted an unprecedented sweep from Feb. 17 to 19 in three towns in Wuhan, where more than 3,300 communities and villages were launched simultaneously.
22日，武汉市政府相关负责人介绍，前期存在的确诊患者没有及时住院救治的问题，已经基本解决。
On February 22, Wuhan government officials introduced that the pre-existing diagnosis of patients did not timely hospital treatment, has been basically resolved.
据湖北卫健委通报，截至2020年2月22日24时，湖北省累计报告新冠肺炎确诊病例64084例，其中：武汉市46201例。
As of 2400 hours on February 22, 2020, a total of 64,084 cases of new crown pneumonia had been reported in Hubei Province, including 46,201 in Wuhan, Hubei Wei Health Commission reported.
全省累计治愈出院15299例,其中：武汉市8171例。
A total of 15,299 cases were cured in the whole province, of which 8171 were in Wuhan.
武汉市累计治愈占累计确诊总量的17.68%。
The cumulative cure rate in Wuhan was 17.68%.
20日、21日，22日，武汉市新增出院数量连续超过新增确诊病例数量。
On the 20th, 21st and 22nd, the number of new discharges from Wuhan city continuously exceeded the number of newly confirmed cases.
